<TITLE> Bus fire death toll rises to seven </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bandarban, Jan 8 (bdnews24.com)  At least seven people were killed and another 45 injured in Bandarban on Friday when a CNG-run picnic bus caught fire and plunged into a roadside ditch, police and witnesses said. Five people were killed on the spot and two others with severe burn injuries died at Chittagong Medical College Hospital. The dead passengers have been identified as Rupak Barua, 35, Shova Barua, 35, Chandan Barua, 35, Happy Barua, 32, and Patu Barua, 70, Milon Barua, 50 and Anika Barua, 50. Witnesses said the bus caught fire in the Manur Tek area of Bandarban-Keranihat road and then fell into the roadside ditch at around 11.30 am. Pulak Barua, a passenger of the bus, told bdnews24.com that all the passengers were residents of Chittagong's Jobra village. Bandarban Sadar thana sub inspector Rafiq Islam said that fire fighters and police reached the spot and rescued the passengers immediately on hearing the accident. bdnews24
